          <msContents>
            <summary>
              <p>Single parchment folio, Shelfmark: 1977.40; Qurʾānic Text:  18: 16-19; Lines per page: 16; Dimensions: 194 x 241 mm; Script style:                                   kūfī (Type B II) ; Estimated date of production:                                   800-900. </p>
              <p> </p>
              <p>The <ref target="https://www.cincinnatiartmuseum.org/art/explore-the-collection?id=23174649">website of the Cincinnati Art Museum</ref> provides the following information about this fragment:  </p>
              <p>"Name: Folio from the Qur’an Describing Several Pious Youth Who Take Refuge in a Cave; Sura al-Kahf (Chapter: The Cave) 18: verses 16–9  Date: 9th Century-10th Century Place: Iraq or Iran Medium: ink on parchment Measurements: 9 1/2 x 7 5/8 in. (24.1 x 19.4 cm) Classification: Manuscript Department: South Asian Art, Islamic Art and Antiquities Credit Line: Fanny Bryce Lehmer Fund  Accession No: 1977.40" </p>
              <p>See the detailed catalogue entry by Marcus Fraser about four sister leaves from the same codex kept at Qatar National Library: <ref target="https://corpuscoranicum.de/handschriften/index/sure/11/vers/116?handschrift=1397">HC.MS.2017.0009</ref>, <ref target="https://corpuscoranicum.de/en/manuscripts/1451/page/1r">HC.MS.03119</ref>, <ref target="https://corpuscoranicum.de/en/manuscripts/1363/page/1r">HC.MS.03167</ref> and  <ref target="https://corpuscoranicum.de/en/manuscripts/1418/page/1r">HC.MS.2017.0010</ref>.  </p>
            </summary>
